Research Review and Pre-Publication Availability Notice

FC-Trace is original research software developed by Vinod Gendre and Nitesh K
Bharadwaj, Department of Computer Science and Engineering, National Institute
of Technology Raipur, India.

This repository snapshot is prepared for conference-paper submission and
reproducibility review. Formal copyright registration is planned separately,
but it is not completed in this pre-publication snapshot.

During the review period, the FC-Trace source code, evaluation scripts,
synthetic ground-truth data, and accompanying artifact package are available
from the authors on reasonable request for academic review and verification of
the reported experimental results. The repository is not intended for public
release at this stage.

Public release and license selection are deferred until after the
copyright-registration process is completed. Until then, no open-source license
is granted. No permission is granted to copy, redistribute, sublicense, sell,
publish, or commercially use this software or substantial portions of it without
prior written permission from the authors.

Researchers who receive access may inspect and execute the code only for
review and reproducibility purposes, provided that this notice remains intact
and the code is not further redistributed.

THE SOFTWARE IS PROVIDED "AS IS", WITHOUT WARRANTY OF ANY KIND, EXPRESS OR
IMPLIED, INCLUDING BUT NOT LIMITED TO THE WARRANTIES OF MERCHANTABILITY, FITNESS
FOR A PARTICULAR PURPOSE AND NONINFRINGEMENT. IN NO EVENT SHALL THE AUTHORS BE
LIABLE FOR ANY CLAIM, DAMAGES, OR OTHER LIABILITY ARISING FROM, OUT OF, OR IN
CONNECTION WITH THE SOFTWARE OR THE USE OR OTHER DEALINGS IN THE SOFTWARE.
